    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-03-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">von Thielmann</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your excellency’s note of to-day’s
                    date, No. 301, I beg to say that I shall thank you for kindly instructing, by
                    telegraph, the United States consul at St. Pierre, Martinique, to extend his
                    protection and render assistance to Captain Aim, master of the German bark <hi
                        rend="italic">Elisabeth Ahrens.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thielmann.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
